// Variables are names or placeholders
// that store values.
// Variables have types:

s:string

// We call this a "declaration".

// `s` is a variable of type string.
// It can hold _any_ string.

// You can give a variable a new value
// with the equal sign `=`.
// We call this "assignment".
s = "Hello, World"

// Assignments of a variable are only
// allowed _after_ its declaration.

// What does this program print‚ùì
print s

